 new Debian package, version 2.0.
 size 18440 bytes: control archive=1076 bytes.
    1182 bytes,    28 lines      control
     325 bytes,     4 lines      md5sums
 Package: libcurl3t64-gnutls
 Source: curl
 Version: 8.11.1.348.gcdbfc2589-20250128.062845986086143
 Architecture: amd64
 Maintainer: Debian Curl Maintainers <team+curl@tracker.debian.org>
 Installed-Size: 45
 Recommends: ca-certificates
 Breaks: libcurl3-gnutls (<< 8.11.1.348.gcdbfc2589-20250128.062845986086143)
 Replaces: libcurl3-gnutls
 Section: libs
 Priority: optional
 Multi-Arch: same
 Homepage: https://curl.se/
 Description: easy-to-use client-side URL transfer library (GnuTLS flavour)
  libcurl is an easy-to-use client-side URL transfer library, supporting DICT,
  FILE, FTP, FTPS, GOPHER, HTTP, HTTPS, IMAP, IMAPS, LDAP, LDAPS, POP3, POP3S,
  RTMP, RTSP, SCP, SFTP, SMTP, SMTPS, TELNET and TFTP.
  .
  libcurl supports SSL certificates, HTTP POST, HTTP PUT, FTP uploading, HTTP
  form based upload, proxies, cookies, user+password authentication (Basic,
  Digest, NTLM, Negotiate, Kerberos), file transfer resume, http proxy tunneling
  and more!
  .
  libcurl is free, thread-safe, IPv6 compatible, feature rich, well supported,
  fast, thoroughly documented and is already used by many known, big and
  successful companies and numerous applications.
  .
  SSL support is provided by GnuTLS.

